How Compilation works in C++? What is Compiler, liner, loader.

Source code(.cpp) --> compiler (.o) --> Linker --> .exe -->Loader --> OS (Running Exe in Memory)
                                          ^                   ^
                                          |                   |
                                        Static Libraries    Dynamic Libraries 
                                        (.lib, .a)          (.dll, .so)
                                        
  Compilation Process consist of 3 stages :
  *****************************************
  Preprocessor (processing of # inlcude directives, macros , inline funcs and replaced symbols) and gives .i file. 
  After .i is being Compiled to created (*.s) 
  assembly code -> Assembler (convert .s to .o) file.
  ** Syntax , semantic erroes are fixed at this stage.
  
Explain memory allocation for C++ program?|
                        

